HEADWORD: Myxomycota
<hw>Myxomycota</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>The slime
molds; organisms having a noncellular and multinucleate creeping
vegetative phase and a propagative spore-producing stage: comprises
Myxomycetes and Acrasiomycetes and Plasmodiophoromycetes; in some
classifications placed in the kingdom Protoctista.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> division Myxomycota, Gymnomycota, division
Gymnomycota.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Myxophyceae</ent>⟦br⟧
